In [29]:
def predict_course(course_name):
    course_user_ratings = course_matrix[course_name]
    similar_to_course = course_matrix.corrwith(course_user_ratings)
    corr_course_name = pd.DataFrame(similar_to_course, columns=['Correlation'])
    corr_course_name.dropna(inplace = True)
    predictions = corr_course_name.sort_values('Correlation', ascending=False)
    return predictions

Making Recommendations using KNN¶

In [43]:
user_rating_pivot = reviews_user.pivot(index="Course", columns="UserId", values="Rating").fillna(0)
user_rating_matrix = csr_matrix(user_rating_pivot.values)
In [44]:
model_knn = NearestNeighbors(metric = 'cosine', algorithm = 'brute')
In [45]:
model_knn.fit(user_rating_matrix)
Out[45]:
NearestNeighbors(algorithm='brute', leaf_size=30, metric='cosine',
                 metric_params=None, n_jobs=None, n_neighbors=5, p=2,
                 radius=1.0)
In [59]:
query_index = np.random.choice(user_rating_pivot.shape[0])
distances, indices = model_knn.kneighbors(user_rating_pivot.iloc[query_index,:].values.reshape(1, -1), n_neighbors = 11)
for i in range(0, len(distances.flatten())):
    if i == 0:
        print('Recommendations for {0}:\n'.format(user_rating_pivot.index[query_index]))
    else:
        print('{0}: {1}, with distance of {2}:'.format(i, user_rating_pivot.index[indices.flatten()[i]], distances.flatten()[i]))
